Detailed Description

Used when defining record formats and when manipulating records. FieldDescriptors are used when defining an input record format for anInputPortDescriptor object, when defining an output record formatfor an OutputPortDescriptor, and when defining both input andoutput record formats for an EnhancementFunctionDescriptor.

Every FieldDescriptor object has a type, chosen from several predefined field types. Every FieldDescriptor object also has a label, which must be unique.

See also:
FieldDescriptorFactory
